Preheat your oven to 220°C. Trim the @butternut squash{1} then halve lengthways and scoop out the seeds. Chop it widthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm chunks (no need to peel!). Lay on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @olive oil{}, sprinkle over the @ground coriander{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread evenly and roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}, turn halfway.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #saucepan{} on medium high heat. Add the onion along with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir together and cook until the onion is soft, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Pour the @water{240%ml} and @vegetable stock powder{1} into the pan with the onion and bring to the boil. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil, pop a lid on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(stalks and all, roughly chopped). Crumble the @feta cheese{75%g} into small chunks. Mix the @honey{15%g}, @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and @olive oil{1}(for the dressing) in a #bowl{} with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Leave to the side.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Add the @sliced spring greens{150%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic to the greens, stir and cook for ~{1%minute} more, then remove from the heat. Once the squash is cooked, stir the squash through the greens either in your #baking tray{} or frying pan - whichever is easiest!

Fluff up the bulgur wheat with a #fork{}, stir in the flat leaf parsley, then taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Spoon into #bowls{} and top with the greens and butternut squash along with the feta. Drizzle the dressing over the top, sprinkle on the @dukkah mix{1} and enjoy.